3.1 AI Tool Usage
VALEO GmbH explicitly permits the use of AI-powered tools and assistants (including but not limited to language models, code generation tools, and automated development assistants) for the analysis, review, and generation of code, documentation, concepts, and other contributions to the Software.

3.2 AI as Internal Contributor
AI systems and tools are recognized as "internal contributors" to the Software development process. Contributions generated or assisted by AI tools are subject to the same review processes, quality standards, and approval workflows as contributions from human developers.

3.3 AI Contribution Tracking
All AI-assisted contributions must be transparently documented and tracked through:
- Commit messages indicating AI involvement (e.g., "[AI-Assisted]", "[AI-Generated]")
- Pull request descriptions noting AI tool usage
- Code comments where AI-generated code is integrated
- Separate changelog entries for AI-driven changes

3.4 Input and Output Restrictions
- Input data provided to AI tools (including training data, code snippets, documentation, and requirements) must originate solely from VALEO-internal sources.
- AI-generated outputs, including code, documentation, and concepts, may only be used within VALEO's internal projects and systems.
- No AI-generated content may be shared, published, or distributed outside of VALEO without explicit written authorization.

